HEADWORD: Householder
<hw>House"hold`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The master or
head of a family; one who occupies a house with his family.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Towns in which almost every <qex>householder</qex> was an English
Protestant.</q> <rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Compound householder</b></col>. <cd>See
<er>Compound</er>, <pos>a.</pos></cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

